INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'a005cce3-3f8e-4ec6-822d-d947088c99f1',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Grafana — Template Variables, Data Links, and Ad-Hoc Filters for Real Interactivity$escape$,
  $escape$Grafana's interactivity model rests on three primitives: template variables, data links, and ad-hoc filters.

Template variables (Dashboard Settings → Variables) inject into any panel query via `${varName}` syntax. For multi-value selectors, append the `:regex` formatter — `${service:regex}` — so Grafana wraps selections in `(svc1|svc2)` for Prometheus label matchers. Back a variable with `label_values(up{env="$env"}, job)` and it auto-populates from live label data, chaining off a parent `$env` variable for cascading dependent filters.

Data links wire panels to drill-down dashboards. In a panel's Data links section, built-in interpolation variables do the heavy lifting: `${__field.name}` captures the series label, `${__value.raw}` the clicked cell value, and `${__url_time_range}` preserves the current window. Pass these as URL params (`var-service=${__field.name}`) to pre-select variables on the target dashboard.

Ad-hoc filters (variable type: Ad hoc filters) automatically inject key=value label matchers into every datasource query on the dashboard — no per-panel wiring required. Pair with a Prometheus or Loki datasource for zero-config cross-panel filtering. For SQL datasources, use `$__timeFilter(time_column)` and `$__from`/`$__to` (epoch ms) for parameterized time range pushdown.$escape$,
  $escape$# 1. Chained template variable (Prometheus)
#    Parent: $env | Child: $service
label_values(up{env="$env"}, job)

# 2. Panel query — multi-value variable with :regex formatter
rate(
  http_requests_total{job=~"${service:regex}", env="$env"}
  [$__rate_interval]
)

# 3. Data link on any time-series or table panel
#    Title: Drill into service
#    URL:   /d/xyz789/service-detail?var-service=${__field.name}&${__url_time_range}$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
